{"body": "I hate to dog-pile on a thread like this, but, well, I almost feel obligated. It boggles my mind that anyone would defend this behavior. I don't mind that it's backwards incompatible. I don't mind that I can't do `request.xhr? == true`. But to justify mindfucking anyone who dares to invoke `request.xhr?` in a debugger with \"the docs don't say it won't do that\" is just plain silliness.\r\n\r\nIf double negation is such a deal breaker, there are plenty of alternative implementations. For example:\r\n\r\n    /XMLHttpRequest/i === @env['HTTP_X_REQUESTED_WITH']", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/4670251", "created_at": "2012-03-24T00:10:10Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/5329#issuecomment-4670251", "updated_at": "2012-03-24T00:10:10Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 5329, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tpope/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tpope/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tpope/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/tpope", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tpope/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/tpope", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tpope/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/67259dd09c53aef920fe2aca18c7a8e0?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F8bf1211fd4b7b94528899de0a43b9fb3.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tpope/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tpope/received_events", "gravatar_id": "67259dd09c53aef920fe2aca18c7a8e0", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tpope/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "tpope", "type": "User", "id": 378, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tpope/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "523819bdbd3543c15100e233"}, "id": 4670251, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/5329"}
